--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a quiz program that allows you to insert new question, delete old ones, and test yourself on them.
Usage is as follows:

> p <qn> :: Use 'p' to insert a new question.
	:: Input question tags as comma separated list
	:: Input question followed by a period: 'question <CR> . <CR>'
	:: Input answer choices as follows: '(<letter>) choice <CR> . <CR>'
	:: When finished inputing choices, enter a second period before the answer
	:: Input letter of correct answer choice
	>> Server will Error if the question already exists for the current meister

> d <qn> :: Use 'd' to delete a question with id == qn
	>> Server will delete the indicated question

> g <qn> :: Use 'g' to see the question with id == qn
	>> Server will output the question as it was input

> s <cn> :: Use 's' to setup a new contest

> b <cn> :: Use 'b' to allocate a socket for a new instance of a contest which runs until finished
	:: Will pass the port number back to the meister
	:: A single contest can have multiple instances of itself started.

> r <qn> :: Use 'r' to review statistics on a set contest
	>> Server will output overall statistics of the contest
	>> If the contest has been run, statistics on each question are provided

> a <cn> <qn> :: Use 'a' to append a question to a set contest
	>> Server outputs an error if either the contest or the question don't exist

> k :: Use 'k' to terminate the server and all clients

> q :: Use 'q' to terminate just the current meister

> h :: Use 'h' to display this page again

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
